         "text": "### The Only Empress\n\nAlthough women and men are both Homo sapiens, it is possible to observe that this equality is rarely recognized by both.\n\n#### An Overview\n\nIn an initial stage, during the Paleolithic—the period between 2.58 million years and 11,700 years ago—we observe, in art, female figures such as the Venus of Willendorf (**Figure 2**), which was related to fertility and deification (<htcite0>; <htcite1>).",
         "source": [
            {
               "type": 1,
               "uuid": "90113e90-d6cd-4204-b78c-17513e9a230c",
               "text": "Britannica Editors",
               "page": "Paleolithic Period",
               "date_time": {
