      {
         "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: Limitations and Achievements</b><br /><br />Clearly, the constitution of living beings was unknown for millennia. However, this was not the only reason for the creation of scenarios in which men ended up being better portrayed and positioned throughout those millennial periods.<br /><br />The past cannot be changed, but now that we understand ourselves better, wouldn't it be fairer for both men and women to have the same rights to achieve equal accomplishments?<br /><br />If the first question made you uncomfortable, reflect once more: would you like to be limited and prevented from reaching your goals, despite possessing full capability to do so?</div></div></center>",
