                  {
                     "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 2: The Next Generation</b><br /><br />Fathers and mothers want the best for their children, even if for different reasons.<br /><br />Now, imagine living in a context where boys are prioritized and girls are raised without the possibility of fully exploring their abilities. In this scenario, you have a daughter.<br /><br />From the moment of her birth, would you act like Wu Shihuo (武士穫) guiding your daughter toward a promising future, or would you align yourself with cultural repression, limiting her developmental possibilities?</div></div></center>",
